The current naming convention (`pr-<number>-review-comments.json`) can cause collisions when working with monorepos that have multiple submodules, each with their own PRs. The new convention includes the repo slug derived from `pr.repo`.

**1. Create repo slug helper function in `src/parser.ts`:**
```typescript
export function getRepoSlug(repo: string): string {
  // repo format: "org/repo-name" -> extract "repo-name"
  const repoName = repo.includes('/') ? repo.split('/').pop()! : repo;
  // Replace special chars with hyphens, lowercase
  return repoName.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-').replace(/^-|-$/g, '');
}
```

**2. Update `findReviewFiles()` in `src/parser.ts` (lines 76-89):**
```typescript
export async function findReviewFiles(reviewsDir: string): Promise<string[]> {
  try {
    const entries = await fs.promises.readdir(reviewsDir);
    return entries
      .filter((f) => {
        // New pattern: <repo-slug>-pr-<number>-review-comments.json
        // Old pattern (backwards compat): pr-<number>-review-comments.json
        return (
          (f.match(/^[a-z0-9-]+-pr-\d+-review-comments\.json$/) ||
           f.match(/^pr-\d+-review-comments\.json$/)) &&
          f.endsWith('-review-comments.json')
        );
      })
      .map((f) => path.join(reviewsDir, f));
  } catch {
    return [];
  }
}
```

